                <div id="how-to-trade">
                    <div class="lg-padding">
                        <div class="row">
                            <div class="col-sm">
                                <h2>[% l('How to trade Forex') %]</h2>
                                <p>[% l('A Forex trader has one objective in mind when trading: to exchange one currency for another in order to make a profit.') %]</p>
                                <p>[% l('But if you’re new to Forex or financial trading of any kind, there\'s still a long way to go before you even purchase your first contract. This is why we\'ve come up with a basic, step-by-step tutorial to help you bridge that gap and make your first trade.') %]</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-sm">
                                <div class="row">
                                    <div class="col-xs">
                                        <img class="float-right" src="[% request.url_for('images/steps.svg') %]">
                                    </div>
                                    <div class="col-xlg">
                                        <h3>[% l('Learn') %]</h3>
                                        <p>[% l('to read currency pairs') %]</p>
                                        <h3>[% l('Understand') %]</h3>
                                        <p>[% l('when to buy (go long) and when to sell (go short') %]</p>
                                        <h3>[% l('Buy') %]</h3>
                                        <p>[% l('your first currency pair') %]</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="lg-padding"></div>
                        <div class="center-text">
                            <h2>[% l('Step 1: Learn to read currency pairs') %]</h2>
                            <p>[% l('Can’t make heads or tails of currency pairs? Here’s a simple way of looking at it:') %]</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="lg-padding">
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-sm">
                                    <div class="txt-right lg-padding">
                                        <h3>EUR</h3>
                                        <h4>[% l('Base currency') %]</h4>
                                        <p>[% l('Also known as transaction currency') %]</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                                <div class="separator-vertical primary-color"></div>
                                <div class="col-sm">
                                    <div class="lg-padding">
                                        <h3>USD</h3>
                                        <h4>[% l('Quote currency') %]</h4>
                                        <p>[% l('Also known as counter currency') %]</p>
                                    </div>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="row lg-padding">
                            <div class="col-sm">
                                <div class="fill-bg-color box">
                                    <h4>[% l('Tips:') %]</h4>
                                </div>
                                <ul class="bullet">
                                    <li>[% l('The base currency is always equal to <strong>one unit</strong>') %].</li>
                                    <li>[% l('The price of the currency pair indicates how much of the quote currency is required to buy one unit of base currency. This is more commonly known as the exchange rate.') %]</li>
                                </ul>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-sm">
                                <div class="fill-bg-color box">
                                    <h4>[% l('Example:') %]</h4>
                                </div>
                                <p>[% l('If you see EUR/USD has a bid price of 1.05229, you’ll sell USD 1.05229 for every EUR 1 that you buy.') %]</p>
                                <p>[% l('If the ask price is 1.05382, you\'ll buy USD 1.05382 for every EUR 1 that you sell.') %]</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <h2 class="center-text">[% l('Step 2: Understand when to buy (go long) and when to sell (go short)') %]</h2>
                        <div class="lg-padding">
                            <p>[% l('You want to buy a certain currency pair if you think the base currency will go up. The reverse holds true: you want to sell that currency pair if you think the base currency will go down.') %]</p>
                            <p>[% l('You’ve probably seen the terms ‘going long’ and ‘going short’ being used by a lot of Forex brokers and traders. Let’s compare the differences between the two terms:') %]</p>
                        </div>

                        <div class="lg-padding">
                            <div class="row">
                                <div class="col-sm">
                                    <h4>[% l('Long') %]</h4>
                                    <div class="separator primary-color"></div>
                                    <ul class="bullet">
                                        <li>[% l('You’re buying the base currency and selling the quote currency.') %]</li>
                                        <li>[% l('You’re expecting the base currency to rise in value so you can sell it back for a profit.') %]</li>
                                        <li>[% l('Go long = buy') %]</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                                <div class="separator-vertical primary-color"></div>
                                <div class="col-sm">
                                    <h4>[% l('Short') %]</h4>
                                    <div class="separator primary-color"></div>
                                    <ul class="bullet">
                                        <li>[% l('You’re selling the base currency and buying the quote currency.') %]</li>
                                        <li>[% l('You’re expecting the base currency to fall in value so you can buy it back at a lower price (and make a profit).') %]</li>
                                        <li>[% l('Go short = sell') %]</li>
                                    </ul>
                                </div>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <div class="box fill-bg-color center-text">
                            <h4>[% l("Here\’s an example: how does going long or going short apply to the GBP/USD?") %]</h4>
                        </div>

                        <div class="row lg-padding">
                            <div class="col-sm">
                                <p>[% l('After your analysis, you’ve come to the conclusion that the British economy will outperform its U.S. counterpart. Thus, you decide to go long and buy into the GBP/USD, expecting the GBP to rise in value.') %]</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-sm">
                                <p>[% l('If you decided that the British economy will underperform instead, then you will go short on the GBP/USD.') %]</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>

                        <h2 class="center-text">[% l('Step 3: Buy your first currency pair') %]</h2>
                        <p class="lg-padding">[% l('After you’ve decided which position you want to take – whether long or short – you are well on your way to buying your first currency pair.') %]</p>

                        <div class="box fill-bg-color center-text">
                            <h4>[% l('Here’s an example of a GBP/USD currency pair and its bid-ask price.') %]</h4>
                        </div>

                        <div class="center-text lg-padding">
                            <img src="[% request.url_for('images/forex-2.png') %]" alt="">
                        </div>

                        <div class="row">
                            <div class="col-sm">
                                <p>[% l('To go long, you’ll click on ‘Buy’ to purchase GBP 1 for USD 1.22781.') %]</p>
                            </div>
                            <div class="col-sm">
                                <p>[% l('To go short, you’ll click on ‘Sell’ to sell GBP 1 and receive USD 1.22771 in return.') %]</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div id="margin-policy">
                    <div class="lg-padding">
                        <h2>[% l('Forex margin policy') %]</h2>
                        <p>[% l('We explain our margin policy to give you a better understanding of how Forex trading works.') %]</p>
                    </div>

                    <div class="row lg-padding">
                        <div class="col-sm">
                            <h3>[% l('What is margin?') %]</h3>
                            <p>[% l('Margin allows you to trade on leverage - giving you the same level of market exposure using much less capital.') %]</p>
                            <p>[% l('With leverage, you can purchase 100 units of the same asset at a fraction of the cost.') %]</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-sm">
                            <div class="box fill-bg-color">
                                <h4>[% l('Example:') %]</h4>
                            </div>
                            <p>[% l('If you wanted to purchase 100 units of a particular asset trading at USD 50 per unit through a traditional broker, it would cost you USD 5,000 for this transaction.') %]</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    [% INCLUDE static/common/separator_line.html.tt %]

                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-sm">
                            <h2>[% l('How is margin calculated?') %]</h2>
                            <p>[% l('The margin for our Forex trades is calculated as follows:') %]</p>
                            <div class="box bordered center-text">
                                <p class="secondary-color">[% l('Volume (lots) x lot size / leverage = <strong>Margin</strong>') %]</p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-sm">
                            <div class="box fill-bg-color">
                                <h4>[% l('Example:') %]</h4>
                            </div>
                            <p>[% l('If you buy one lot of the EUR/USD symbol with a contract size of 100,000 and leverage of 100:1, the margin required to purchase that one lot will be calculated as follows:') %]</p>
                            <p class="secondary-color">1 x 100,000 / 100 = EUR 1,000</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    [% INCLUDE static/common/separator_line.html.tt %]

                    <div class="row">
                        <div class="col-sm">
                            <h2>[% l("What\’s a margin call and how do we apply it?") %]</h2>
                            <div class="separator primary-color"></div>
                            <p>[% l('When your account equity is unable to cover the margin requirement, your account will be placed under margin call. This state does not affect your ability to open new positions') %]</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-sm">
                            <h2>[% l("What\’s a stop out level and how do we apply it?") %]</h2>
                            <div class="separator primary-color"></div>
                            <p>[% l("If your account is placed under margin call for an extended period of time, it will reach the stop out level where it\’s unable to sustain an open position. This will lead to your pending orders being deleted, and open positions being forcibly closed (also known as forced liquidation).") %]</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>

                    <p class="lg-padding">[% l('Once your account hits the forced liquidation level, your orders and positions are forcibly closed in the following order:') %]</p>
                    <ul class="bullet">
                        <li>[% l('We analyse your pending orders.') %]</li>
                        <li>[% l('We delete an order with the largest margin reserved.') %]</li>
                        <li>[% l('If your margin level is still under the stop out level, your next order will be deleted. However, orders without margin requirements will not be deleted.') %]</li>
                        <li>[% l('If your margin level is still under the stop out level, we will close an open position with the largest loss.') %]</li>
                        <li>[% l('We will continue to close open positions until your margin level becomes higher than the stop out level.') %]</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>

