                    <div class="row lg-padding no-gutters">
                        <div class="col-sm">
                            <h4>[% l('1. Account currency') %]</h4>
                            <div class="separator primary-color"></div>
                            <p>[% l('Is the currency of the funds accepted in your trading account.') %]</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-sm">
                            <h4>[% l('2. Leverage') %]</h4>
                            <div class="separator primary-color"></div>
                            <p>[% l('Is the ability to control a large amount of money using a minimal capital from yourself. Where does the rest of the money come from? Your trusted broker provides the rest.') %]</p>
                            <p>[% l('Let’s say you fork out a capital of USD 50 and we’re offering a leverage of 1:1,000. How much money, or margin, is available to you when you start trading?') %]</p>
                            <div class="box bordered">
                                <p class="secondary-color">USD 50 x 1,000 = <strong>USD 50,000 [% l('(is the margin available)') %]</strong></p>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-sm">
                            <h4>[% l('3. Order execution') %]</h4>
                            <div class="separator primary-color"></div>
                            <p>[% l('Typically comes in two varieties: market execution and instant execution. With market execution, you place an order at the broker’s price. You agree on the price in advance. There are no requotes with market execution.') %]</p>
                            <p>[% l('What about instant execution? In this case, your order is place at the price that’s available at that time. Requotes are possible if the price fluctuates a great deal before the order execution is complete.') %]</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="row lg-padding no-gutters">
                        <div class="col-sm">
                            <h4>[% l('4. Spread') %]</h4>
                            <div class="separator primary-color"></div>
                            <p>[% l('Is the difference between the buy price and sell price. When you enter into a trade, you are buying an asset that you will be selling at a later time or date for a profit or loss. The difference in price is called a spread. A fixed spread means that the spread will remain as it is no matter the market condition. A variable spread means that the spread may increase depending on market conditions, as it is subject to market volatility caused by news events.') %]</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-sm">
                            <h4>[% l('5. Commission') %]</h4>
                            <div class="separator primary-color"></div>
                            <p>[% l('Refers to the commission fees that we charge for each trade you place with us. ChampionFX currently charges no commission for all accounts.') %]</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-sm">
                            <h4>[% l('6. Margin call') %]</h4>
                            <div class="separator primary-color"></div>
                            <p>[% l('Refers to the state where the remaining funds in your account is unable to cover the leverage or margin requirement. You can deposit additional funds to prevent a margin call escalating to a stop out level.') %]</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="row lg-padding no-gutters">
                        <div class="col-sm">
                            <h4>[% l('7. Stop out level') %]</h4>
                            <div class="separator primary-color"></div>
                            <p>[% l('Is the level where your margin ratio has become unsustainable, and we issue a forced closure of pending orders, and any open positions. A stop out level usually results from a high negative balance in your trading account.') %]</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-sm">
                            <h4>[% l('8. Hedged margin') %]</h4>
                            <div class="separator primary-color"></div>
                            <p>[% l('Refers to the funds required to open and maintain a position on the same asset, but in opposite directions.') %]</p>
                        </div>
                        <div class="col-sm">
                            <h4>[% l('9. A swap-free option') %]</h4>
